  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6778.6 sitting just below the massive +10967.5M gamma wall at 6780 (also the flip strike), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push through this level while providing strong support on dips toward the -6241.9M gamma pit at 6770. The PIN regime combined with the towering positive gamma walls at 6780/6800 creates a powerful mean-reversion setup, with dealers acting as liquidity providers who will fade directional moves. Key levels to watch are the 6770 negative gamma floor (where dealer buying accelerates) and the 6780-6800 positive gamma ceiling (where dealer selling intensifies).\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pinned between 6770-6780 with strong resistance to big moves in either direction.",
